quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  27,77,"and most surely it is a guidance and a mercy to the believers."
  27,78,"Indeed, your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord decrees between them by His wise judgment, and He is the Almighty, the All-Knowing."
  27,79,"So place your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>trust in Allah; you are indeed upon the evident truth."
  27,80,"Indeed, you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>cannot make the dead hear, nor can <span class=""h"">you make<sup foot_note=""80755"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">the deaf hear</span>the call if they withdraw and turn their backs."
  27,81,"Nor <span class=""h"">can you</span><a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a><span class=""h"">guide<sup foot_note=""80756"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>the blind out of their utter misguidance; you can make no one hear except those who believe in Our signs, and are<i class=""s"">(thus) </i>Muslims{2}.",footnotes:2:The Arabic word used is Muslimoonwhich means those who willingly submit to God, regardless of which prophet they followed.
  27,82,"And when the decree is fulfilled against them, We will bring out for them—from the earth—a treading creature that will <span class=""h"">tell them that<sup foot_note=""80758"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">mankind</span>used to have no certitude in Our signs."
  27,83,"On the day when We herd from every community a crowd of those who disbelieve our signs, so that they are held in strict order."
  27,84,"Until, when they come<i class=""s"">(before their Lord) </i>, He will say, “Did you deny My signs and did you not encompass them in knowledge, or what were you doing?”"
  27,85,"And the decree shall be fulfilled against them for the injustices they did, and they shall be speechless."
  27,86,"Have they not seen that We have made the night for them to rest therein and the day allowing sight? Indeed, in that are signs for people who believe."
  27,87,"And on the day when the Trumpet is blown, and everyone in the heavens and the earth was{1}horrified, except whomever Allah willed, and everyone came before Him in humility.",footnotes:1:Frequently the Qur’an addresses the events of the hereafter in pasttense; this grammatical shift should be pondered by the reader.
  27,88,"And you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>see the mountains, thinking them fixed, yet they pass as the passing of the clouds—the making of Allah Who has perfected everything; He is indeed All-Aware of what <span class=""h"">you<sup foot_note=""80760"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">do</span>."
